snippet: The report on unemployment added to a range of data that suggested higher taxes were having a limited impact on the economy.
abstract: Labor Department reports that weekly claims for state unemployment benefits dropped 10,000, to a seasonally adjusted 332,000; figure, lower than analyst expectations, is latest sign that labor market recovery is gaining traction.
lead_paragraph: The report on unemployment added to a range of data that suggested higher taxes were having a limited impact on the economy.

headline.seo: New Jobless Claims Drop for Third Straight Week
headline.main: New Jobless Claims at a 5-Year Low
headline.print_headline: New Jobless Claims at a 5-Year Low
